         <abstract>
            <p>The matrices occurring in the equations of inviscid fluid dynamics are simultaneously symmetrized by a similarity transformation. The resulting matrices decompose into several lower-dimensional blocks. In addition these blocks are more sparse than previously obtained. These properties are then used to find a sufficiency proof for an improved version of the two-step Richtmyer method.</p>
          </abstract>
